snippet.textDisplay:
I don't blame them for not trying... To be honest, the people who still want a Youtube Rewind should be lucky that they got one cause if I was the one making decisions on Youtube, there would be no Youtube Rewind 2019, 2020 or Youtube Rewind anything in the future. Even when it was still good, I never really saw the point of it, even when people were raving about it. I just watch my favourite youtubers talk about it cause there is nothing else to watch on youtube during that time. Youtube is surprisingly really boring in November December and January the next year.


Edit: Also, I know everybody is going to disagree with me on this, but as someone who is planning on starting a proper youtube channel next year, I'm actually excited for the new Youtube. I don't think it's going to be that big of a problem at all actually. BECAUSE NOW YOU'RE ALLOWED TO BE INAPPROPRIATE AGAIN!! I've listened to many youtubers complaints and personally, I don't see what's the problem. This is what people have been wanting for a long time, why are we sad that they're allowing us to be vulgar again next year? If there really is anybody being punished, it's the child friendly people who we should be feeling sorry for... But I don't know... I've been thinking about streaming on Twitch instead of youtube for sometime so... I'm just saying, I think that if Youtube can do this Coppa thing properly, it could actually benefit everybody, especially since they already allow us to age restrict our own content.

snippet.textDisplay:
I posted this on the Rewind video and I still think it's true -

Dear YouTube,

Get a creator or a group of creators on YouTube to direct your Rewind videos. You're business people, which is evidenced by how last year you spent a lot of money directing a tone deaf commercial directed at people who already use YouTube and this year your stand-out play it safe idea was to save money on production by letting the number of views on your videos dictate the content of your Rewind creation.

There's a reason there's a disconnect between the people that run YouTube (you) and the people that use YouTube (creators) and as Rewind's progress it's becoming ever more evident that the divide is growing not shrinking. We get it. You're a business but you don't just rely on creatives they are the foundation stone for the bridge that transports money from corporations with advertising campaigns to people that watch creators.

You are the architects and custodians of that bridge and it is showing signs of wear and tear. Your maintenance cannot focus on what goes across the bridge, it must focus on the substance of the bridge. Talk to the stones, the creators, if you don't, someone will build a new bridge and everything you have will collapse. If you lack direction appoint a Creator Council of YouTubers large and small from across the world and your platform and ask them questions.

Not guarded, vague questions but pointed questions that have meaning and will affect how you approach things, how you do things. Stop acting. Stop making. Stop managing. Listen and be seen to listen. If you don't, eventually, someone else will. You're the biggest because you were first not because you're the best, one day competition will be fierce and all the time you waste now will be to the detriment of yourselves, your creators and your audience but most importantly to your business, to all of your advertisers.

Get it right, make it strong or be replaced. That's entertainment.

Good luck,

M
